1
00:00:01,780 --> 00:00:03,990
♪♪

2
00:00:30,150 --> 00:00:34,450
Jotaro: Yeah, we've taken care of Angelo for good.

3
00:00:34,480 --> 00:00:37,190
But it'll be a while 'til I'm back.

4
00:00:37,220 --> 00:00:40,390
About that other photo we've been looking into,

5
00:00:40,420 --> 00:00:43,130
if you would, please send it over to me.

6
00:00:43,160 --> 00:00:45,360
That's right, from Egypt,

7
00:00:45,390 --> 00:00:48,530
the one the speedwagon foundation found ten years ago.

8
00:00:48,560 --> 00:00:51,130
I think I might have figured it out.

9
00:00:51,170 --> 00:00:52,300
Later, then.

10
00:00:53,570 --> 00:00:57,540
And ironically it's all thanks to him.

11
00:00:58,970 --> 00:01:01,240
Angelo: Josuke, let's be frank.

12
00:01:01,280 --> 00:01:03,210
Yeah, I murdered your grandpa,

13
00:01:03,250 --> 00:01:05,510
but that doesn't mean you can put me to death, too!

14
00:01:05,550 --> 00:01:07,380
If you kill me, you'll end up cursed,

15
00:01:07,420 --> 00:01:09,120
just like yours truly,

16
00:01:09,150 --> 00:01:11,850
so back off if you know what's good for you! ( Laughs )

17
00:01:11,890 --> 00:01:13,860
- Shining diamond: Dora! - ( Angelo screams )

18
00:01:13,890 --> 00:01:16,490
Josuke: It's rude to point your finger at people.

19
00:01:16,530 --> 00:01:18,260
Didn't your mother ever teach you that?

20
00:01:18,290 --> 00:01:19,600
( Angelo gasps )

21
00:01:19,630 --> 00:01:23,270
What the hell did you do to my hand?!

22
00:01:23,300 --> 00:01:24,530
Josuke: You should take solace

23
00:01:24,570 --> 00:01:26,870
in the fact no one's gonna execute you,

24
00:01:26,900 --> 00:01:28,470
not me and not this guy either.

25
00:01:28,500 --> 00:01:31,010
We won't be killing you,

26
00:01:31,040 --> 00:01:34,110
nor will we be turning you in to the police.

27
00:01:34,140 --> 00:01:36,050
Jotaro: Josuke, you handle the rest.

28
00:01:36,080 --> 00:01:37,280
Angelo: What the hell

29
00:01:37,310 --> 00:01:39,480
are you psychotic bastards planning to do?!

30
00:01:39,520 --> 00:01:42,420
Josuke: Enjoy your eternal penance, Angelo.

31
00:01:42,450 --> 00:01:44,150
Reflect on the life you stole

32
00:01:44,190 --> 00:01:47,020
from my grandpa and all the others!

33
00:01:47,060 --> 00:01:49,460
( Shining diamond yelling )

34
00:01:54,130 --> 00:01:57,630
( Angelo groans ) Damn you bastards all to hell!

35
00:01:57,670 --> 00:02:01,140
I wouldn't get cocky, you little shit-head!

36
00:02:01,170 --> 00:02:03,270
You think you've won, but he'll be here

37
00:02:03,310 --> 00:02:06,240
to butcher you into bloody pieces soon enough!

38
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:08,010
Josuke: What? Who is "he"?

39
00:02:08,040 --> 00:02:09,950
Angelo: Oh, you'll find out.

40
00:02:09,980 --> 00:02:11,480
He wears a school uniform,

41
00:02:11,510 --> 00:02:13,880
and he's the one who gave me this power.

42
00:02:13,920 --> 00:02:15,320
( Jotaro gasps ) Hang on.

43
00:02:15,350 --> 00:02:18,120
You're saying that there's someone out there

44
00:02:18,150 --> 00:02:20,390
who can bestow the power of a stand?

45
00:02:20,420 --> 00:02:22,460
Angelo: Scared? ( Laughs )

46
00:02:22,490 --> 00:02:25,430
Josuke: Yeah, nice try, pal, but what's so scary about that?

47
00:02:25,460 --> 00:02:27,400
Jotaro: Wait. He's telling the truth

48
00:02:27,430 --> 00:02:29,270
about not being born a stand user.

49
00:02:29,300 --> 00:02:33,470
Thing is, no one knew how he obtained his powers.

50
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:34,540
Just think about it.

51
00:02:34,570 --> 00:02:36,270
What if there really is a person

52
00:02:36,310 --> 00:02:38,070
who can impart stands to others?

53
00:02:38,110 --> 00:02:39,910
Angelo: Petrifying thought, isn't it?

54
00:02:39,940 --> 00:02:42,680
( Chuckles ) Do you wanna know more?

55
00:02:42,710 --> 00:02:44,110
( Laughs )

56
00:02:44,150 --> 00:02:48,320
It happened last year, 1998, about a month

57
00:02:48,350 --> 00:02:51,450
before my execution was to be carried out.

58
00:02:51,490 --> 00:02:54,460
I remember that night well.

59
00:02:54,490 --> 00:02:59,160
It was cloudy, and I couldn't sleep worth a damn,

60
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:04,100
so I just sat there staring off into the darkness.

61
00:03:04,130 --> 00:03:08,600
It was quiet, dead quiet.

62
00:03:08,640 --> 00:03:11,040
Then all of a sudden, it happened.

63
00:03:12,680 --> 00:03:16,450
In that shitty excuse for a solitary cell,

64
00:03:16,480 --> 00:03:19,110
there he was...

65
00:03:19,150 --> 00:03:22,050
The guy in the school uniform.

66
00:03:22,080 --> 00:03:25,220
( Gasps ) What the hell? Who let you in here?!

67
00:03:25,250 --> 00:03:27,420
Where'd you come from?!

68
00:03:28,660 --> 00:03:30,260
Wha...

69
00:03:30,290 --> 00:03:33,400
He was holding an ancient bow and arrow.

70
00:03:33,430 --> 00:03:34,660
From the looks of 'em,

71
00:03:34,700 --> 00:03:37,270
they must have been hundreds of years old.

72
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:39,400
What are you doing?! What the hell?!

73
00:03:39,440 --> 00:03:41,270
I was scared shitless.

74
00:03:41,300 --> 00:03:44,270
It was like my balls crawled into my stomach.

75
00:03:44,310 --> 00:03:46,210
But before I could let out a scream...

76
00:03:47,210 --> 00:03:49,140
( Gurgles )

77
00:03:53,180 --> 00:03:54,550
♪♪

78
00:04:10,300 --> 00:04:11,370
( Gurgles )

79
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:13,100
Man: Congratulations.

80
00:04:13,140 --> 00:04:14,270
You survived.

81
00:04:14,300 --> 00:04:17,210
And what's more, you have talent.

82
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:19,280
Otherwise, you'd be dead right now.

83
00:04:20,780 --> 00:04:25,080
As of this moment, you've acquired a special ability.

84
00:04:25,110 --> 00:04:27,080
Or perhaps I should simply say

85
00:04:27,120 --> 00:04:30,090
that I extracted it from your soul.

86
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:33,420
The more wicked the criminal, the more talent he holds.

87
00:04:33,460 --> 00:04:35,690
It's a talent that a man named dio

88
00:04:35,720 --> 00:04:39,030
once referred to as a "stand."

89
00:04:39,060 --> 00:04:41,560
( Aqua necklace yells )

90
00:04:43,170 --> 00:04:45,430
Jotaro: Dio? That's what he said?

91
00:04:45,470 --> 00:04:47,270
Josuke: Is something the matter, Mr. Jotaro?

92
00:04:47,300 --> 00:04:50,540
( Boy screaming )

93
00:04:50,570 --> 00:04:52,570
- Josuke: What the-- - Angelo: You idiots!

94
00:04:52,610 --> 00:04:55,040
You were so captivated by my story,

95
00:04:55,080 --> 00:04:57,280
you completely forgot about my aqua necklace!

96
00:04:57,310 --> 00:04:58,580
Jotaro: Angelo, you bastard!

97
00:04:58,610 --> 00:05:00,020
Angelo: Josuke, you've lost,

98
00:05:00,380 --> 00:05:03,050
so get me the hell outta this rock!

99
00:05:03,090 --> 00:05:05,190
( Boy gagging )

100
00:05:05,220 --> 00:05:07,060
Josuke: I might have considered it,

101
00:05:07,090 --> 00:05:11,060
if this pathetic show of yours was actually making me mad.

102
00:05:11,090 --> 00:05:12,430
Angelo: What are you doing?!

103
00:05:12,460 --> 00:05:15,130
I told you to get me outta this stupid rock!

104
00:05:15,160 --> 00:05:16,670
If you don't get a move on,

105
00:05:16,700 --> 00:05:19,300
you and your prissy-ass hair are gettin' ripped apart!

106
00:05:19,340 --> 00:05:21,070
- ( Josuke grunts ) - ( Jotaro grunts )

107
00:05:21,100 --> 00:05:22,770
Josuke: You wanna repeat that?

108
00:05:22,810 --> 00:05:24,410
Jotaro: Take it easy, josuke!

109
00:05:24,440 --> 00:05:26,640
Josuke: What did you call my hair?!

110
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:29,140
Angelo: If you kill me, the guy in the school uniform

111
00:05:29,180 --> 00:05:31,480
is just gonna hunt you down and do the same to you!

112
00:05:31,510 --> 00:05:33,780
I didn't say earlier, but he lives in this town, too!

113
00:05:33,820 --> 00:05:36,650
Jotaro: Say what? Josuke, stand down!

114
00:05:36,690 --> 00:05:39,620
( Shining diamond yells )

115
00:05:41,490 --> 00:05:43,530
♪♪

116
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:47,500
Jotaro: Hmm?

117
00:05:52,840 --> 00:05:57,340
Josuke: I'll give him this, he managed to piss me off.

118
00:05:57,370 --> 00:05:59,880
So I thought it was only fair to repay the dick-wad

119
00:05:59,910 --> 00:06:03,380
by turning him into a great work of art.

120
00:06:03,410 --> 00:06:05,150
( Boy sobbing )

121
00:06:05,180 --> 00:06:07,580
( Jotaro sighs ) Good grief, kid.

122
00:06:07,620 --> 00:06:10,690
We needed to keep him talking a little longer.

123
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:12,390
Josuke: Huh? Please don't tell me

124
00:06:12,420 --> 00:06:13,790
you believed any of that crap.

125
00:06:13,820 --> 00:06:16,190
Jotaro: You bet. Or didn't you hear him

126
00:06:16,230 --> 00:06:17,890
when he was going on about dio?

127
00:06:17,930 --> 00:06:20,360
Jotaro: Yeah, I heard him. Who is he?

128
00:06:20,400 --> 00:06:22,500
Jotaro: The joestars's greatest enemy.

129
00:06:22,530 --> 00:06:25,470
Our family was fighting him for over a hundred years.

130
00:06:25,500 --> 00:06:27,740
It all came to a head ten years ago

131
00:06:27,770 --> 00:06:29,470
when we defeated him.

132
00:06:29,510 --> 00:06:33,380
But there's one thing none of us could ever figure out.

133
00:06:33,410 --> 00:06:35,510
Dio didn't have a stand in the past,

134
00:06:35,540 --> 00:06:37,680
so how the hell did he suddenly gain

135
00:06:37,710 --> 00:06:40,250
such a powerful one in 1987?

136
00:06:40,280 --> 00:06:43,220
Josuke: I see. You think he got it from the same guy.

137
00:06:43,250 --> 00:06:45,890
Jotaro: Yeah. I think we may have found a new enemy

138
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:47,620
in this school uniform guy.

139
00:06:47,660 --> 00:06:49,660
Or it could be that the bow and arrow

140
00:06:49,690 --> 00:06:51,790
is the source of this madness.

141
00:06:53,930 --> 00:06:57,900
If he was right and it's hiding somewhere in this town,

142
00:06:57,930 --> 00:07:00,770
then Angelo was just the opening act

143
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:03,310
in a horror show of epic proportions.

144
00:07:05,270 --> 00:07:07,440
Good grief.

145
00:07:16,290 --> 00:07:18,850
Koichi: It's like Mr. Jotaro said.

146
00:07:18,890 --> 00:07:20,960
Jotaro: See for yourself.

147
00:07:20,990 --> 00:07:23,190
There's something evil lurking in this town.

148
00:07:23,230 --> 00:07:26,360
Catastrophic danger's closing in as we speak.

149
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:28,860
No, it's already here.

150
00:07:28,900 --> 00:07:31,370
Koichi: The number of missing persons

151
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:34,740
reported in morioh has risen to 81 in this year alone...

152
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:38,410
45 of which were children.

153
00:07:38,440 --> 00:07:40,810
Even if some were runaways, that's still

154
00:07:40,840 --> 00:07:43,910
seven to eight times more than the national average.

155
00:07:43,950 --> 00:07:45,710
It's outrageous.

156
00:07:45,750 --> 00:07:47,320
Also...

157
00:07:48,750 --> 00:07:51,720
Josuke's grandfather.

158
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:54,490
Josuke: School's out, koichi.

159
00:07:54,520 --> 00:07:56,390
Why are you still studying there?

160
00:07:56,430 --> 00:07:57,490
Let's go home.

161
00:07:58,530 --> 00:08:00,400
Koichi: Oh, sure.

162
00:08:01,560 --> 00:08:02,730
That's a relief.

163
00:08:02,760 --> 00:08:05,000
Josuke seems to be feeling better.

164
00:08:11,770 --> 00:08:13,740
Josuke: Yo, Angelo.

165
00:08:13,780 --> 00:08:16,480
Koichi: Uh, hey, has this rock always been here?

166
00:08:16,510 --> 00:08:19,680
Josuke: Yeah, but it's been given a...Face-lift.

167
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:20,880
Koichi: Face-lift?

168
00:08:20,920 --> 00:08:22,450
Hmm.

169
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:24,820
Well, what do you know? Yo, Angelo.

170
00:08:24,850 --> 00:08:25,850
( Angelo grunts )

171
00:08:27,290 --> 00:08:28,890
Koichi: I've been meaning to ask,

172
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:30,860
- what happened to Mr. Jotaro? - Josuke: Hmm?

173
00:08:30,890 --> 00:08:33,760
Oh, he said there was some stuff he needed to look into,

174
00:08:33,800 --> 00:08:35,860
so he went back over to the grand hotel.

175
00:08:35,900 --> 00:08:37,970
Koichi: Do you think it has to do with the town?

176
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:40,600
Josuke: Sure seems like it.

177
00:08:40,640 --> 00:08:41,970
Koichi: I see.

178
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:44,070
♪♪

179
00:08:46,310 --> 00:08:48,980
We're facing a crisis.

180
00:08:56,490 --> 00:08:58,350
Huh?

181
00:08:58,390 --> 00:08:59,790
I think that's a--

182
00:08:59,820 --> 00:09:01,220
hey, josuke.

183
00:09:01,260 --> 00:09:02,290
Josuke: What?

184
00:09:02,320 --> 00:09:03,790
Koichi: I could be wrong,

185
00:09:03,830 --> 00:09:06,030
but hasn't this house been abandoned for a few years?

186
00:09:07,830 --> 00:09:10,370
Josuke: Yeah, I doubt anyone would buy this eyesore.

187
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:13,440
They'd be better off bulldozing it and starting over.

188
00:09:13,470 --> 00:09:15,640
Koichi: Well, maybe they just moved in.

189
00:09:15,670 --> 00:09:17,440
When I looked up at the window,

190
00:09:17,470 --> 00:09:19,540
I could have sworn I saw someone.

191
00:09:19,580 --> 00:09:21,880
Josuke: Huh? But that's impossible.

192
00:09:21,910 --> 00:09:23,550
Did you forget where I live?

193
00:09:23,580 --> 00:09:25,910
I'd have noticed if someone moved in.

194
00:09:25,950 --> 00:09:28,650
And besides, I always see real-estate guys

195
00:09:28,680 --> 00:09:30,690
patrolling the area, looking for squatters.

196
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:33,920
Koichi: Hmm. I guess that makes sense.

197
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:36,930
How peculiar. I hate to say it,

198
00:09:36,960 --> 00:09:39,560
but maybe I saw a ghost. Freaky.

199
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:40,730
Josuke: Come on, dude.

200
00:09:40,760 --> 00:09:42,600
Knock it off with crap like that.

201
00:09:42,630 --> 00:09:43,900
Ghosts give me the willies.

202
00:09:43,930 --> 00:09:45,670
Not to mention I live right there.

203
00:09:47,540 --> 00:09:49,070
♪♪

204
00:09:49,100 --> 00:09:50,370
( Koichi gasps )

205
00:09:50,410 --> 00:09:51,970
( Gagging )

206
00:09:54,410 --> 00:09:56,680
Man: Try keeping your nose out of other people's business,

207
00:09:56,710 --> 00:09:57,910
little brat.

208
00:09:58,980 --> 00:10:00,020
Nothing to say?

209
00:10:00,780 --> 00:10:02,120
Josuke: Koichi, no!

210
00:10:02,150 --> 00:10:04,090
Hey! What the hell do you think you're doing?!

211
00:10:04,120 --> 00:10:07,620
Man: What? I should be the one asking you that question.

212
00:10:07,660 --> 00:10:10,630
You and your friend are on my property.

213
00:10:23,170 --> 00:10:25,940
( Doorbell rings )

214
00:10:27,340 --> 00:10:29,340
( Doorbell rings )

215
00:10:29,380 --> 00:10:31,110
Tomoko: Enough!

216
00:10:31,150 --> 00:10:33,920
If it's about the newspaper, I said we don't want any!

217
00:10:36,550 --> 00:10:38,190
( Doorbell rings )

218
00:10:38,220 --> 00:10:40,190
What's your problem?!

219
00:10:40,220 --> 00:10:42,420
Look, buddy, I just lost my dad to a stroke,

220
00:10:42,460 --> 00:10:43,990
and I'm still trying to figure out

221
00:10:44,030 --> 00:10:45,990
what the hell my family's going to do, okay?

222
00:10:46,030 --> 00:10:47,930
Come back later!

223
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:50,000
( Gasps ) Y-you're...

224
00:10:50,030 --> 00:10:51,470
( Jotaro sighs )

225
00:10:53,440 --> 00:10:55,240
Tomoko: Jo...

226
00:10:55,270 --> 00:10:57,540
Joseph!

227
00:10:57,570 --> 00:11:01,040
You finally came back for me after all of these years!

228
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:02,940
I've been waiting for you!

229
00:11:02,980 --> 00:11:04,910
Since dad died, it's been like living

230
00:11:04,950 --> 00:11:07,050
in an endless sea of depression!

231
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:09,520
You came when I needed you most, Joseph, my love!

232
00:11:09,550 --> 00:11:11,020
( Jotaro sighs )

233
00:11:11,050 --> 00:11:12,990
Tomoko: I love, love, love, love, love, love,

234
00:11:13,020 --> 00:11:14,220
love, love, love, love, love, love...

235
00:11:14,260 --> 00:11:16,220
Jotaro: I'm sorry to disappoint you,

236
00:11:16,260 --> 00:11:18,560
but I'm not the joestar you're looking for.

237
00:11:18,590 --> 00:11:20,030
Tomoko: Eh?

238
00:11:20,060 --> 00:11:22,430
Jotaro: You see? Not a wrinkle on my face.

239
00:11:22,460 --> 00:11:26,640
Tomoko: Oh. Oh, now that you mention it,

240
00:11:26,670 --> 00:11:28,440
you do look younger.

241
00:11:28,470 --> 00:11:30,410
Jotaro: Good grief.

242
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:32,070
I'm Joseph's grandson.

243
00:11:32,110 --> 00:11:34,240
My name is jotaro kujo.

244
00:11:34,280 --> 00:11:36,450
Tomoko: Oh. His grandson, huh?

245
00:11:36,480 --> 00:11:39,150
Jotaro: Josuke'll tell you the rest of the story.

246
00:11:39,180 --> 00:11:43,220
Tedious chitchat drives me up the wall.

247
00:11:43,250 --> 00:11:46,460
Speaking of josuke, is he around?

248
00:11:46,490 --> 00:11:48,460
( Tomoko sighs )

249
00:11:50,230 --> 00:11:52,460
Jotaro: Hmm? Are you listening?

250
00:11:52,490 --> 00:11:54,200
I asked where josuke is.

251
00:11:54,230 --> 00:11:57,330
Tomoko: Uh, oh, well, the school day just ended,

252
00:11:57,370 --> 00:11:59,430
so he isn't home yet.

253
00:11:59,470 --> 00:12:02,500
Jotaro: I see. Then, I'll be back tonight.

254
00:12:02,540 --> 00:12:05,340
Tomoko: Wait. You're leaving already?

255
00:12:08,410 --> 00:12:11,150
Jotaro: Oh. About your father...

256
00:12:11,180 --> 00:12:12,280
Tomoko: Eh?

257
00:12:12,310 --> 00:12:14,050
Jotaro: His death was a real shame.

258
00:12:14,080 --> 00:12:15,680
If Joseph joestar were here,

259
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:17,550
he'd protect you with his life.

260
00:12:17,590 --> 00:12:20,590
I'm sure he'd leap into danger if it meant keeping you safe.

261
00:12:20,620 --> 00:12:22,990
But he's an old man now.

262
00:12:23,020 --> 00:12:25,590
It'd be irresponsible to let him come here.

263
